Name: Yuri
AboutMe:
Graduated MSC Computing Science at the Rijksuniversiteit Groningen, Netherlands.

I have performed my graduation thesis on the field of Image Compression using Dense Field Skeletons. This is image compression using shapes, rather than individual pixels. This has the advantage that we can assign importance on a different level than before.

I am currently employed as a Software Engineer for CIMSolutions B.V.

Previously I was an assistant teacher at the university, and have assisted the following courses:

  • Imperative Programming ( C )
  • Software Analysis and Design (UML)
  • Algorithms and Data Structures in C
  • Parallel Computing ( C )
  • Introduction to Intelligent Systems ( Matlab )
  • Image Processing ( Matlab )
